<subSubSection id="C3156577FFDFFF97FF47F93CFD69F8B6" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDFFF97FF47F93CFD69F8B6" blockId="3.[163,780,1762,1906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FF47F93CFEC0F933" box="[163,285,1762,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Etymology:</emphasis>
The genus name is the combination of 
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FD2DF93DFCD8F93C" box="[713,773,1763,1784]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">scopa</emphasis>
, broom in Latin, after the clustered clavate spicules on the palpal retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), and the Greek suffix -μεγόψ, magnification, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FD87F8E1FCD9F890" box="[611,772,1855,1876]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FD87F8E1FCD9F890" box="[611,772,1855,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Lagonomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus id="54B4885EFFDFFF97FF47F883FF0EF8B6" box="[163,211,1885,1906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">type</typeStatus>
genus of the family. The name is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFDFFF97FCDFFF18FAD0FF1E" box="[827,1293,197,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDFFF97FCDFFF18FAD0FF1E" blockId="3.[827,1293,197,219]" box="[827,1293,197,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFF18FB75FF1F" box="[827,1192,197,219]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<typeStatus id="54B4885EFFDFFF97FCDFFF18FCADFF1F" box="[827,880,198,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC35FF1BFB75FF1F" authority="Guo &amp; Selden &amp; Ren, 2022" authorityName="Guo &amp; Selden &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2022" box="[977,1192,197,219]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fax" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC35FF1BFB75FF1F" bold="true" box="[977,1192,197,219]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops fax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2485795FFDFFF97FB54FF1BFAD0FF1E" box="[1200,1293,197,218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFDFFF97FCDFFF34FAA0FE9F" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDFFF97FCDFFF34FAA0FE9F" blockId="3.[827,1443,233,347]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFF34FC6FFF3B" box="[827,946,234,255]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Male palpal tibia with a small apophysis on the distal retrolateral surface, several clustered clavate spicules situated on the top of retrolateral apophysis; leg metatarsus distinctly much longer than tarsus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3156577FFDFFF97FCDFFE5AFB8BF9CC" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDFFF97FCDFFE5AFABCFC66" blockId="3.[827,1444,388,1544]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFE5AFC65FE5D" box="[827,952,388,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Remarks:</emphasis>
CNU-ARA-MA2 0 2 0 0 0 1 is an adult male. It can be easily distinguished from other male lagonomegopids by the apophysis on the distal retrolateral surface of the male palpal tibia. It cannot be included in the two lagonomegopid genera (
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC4DFDC3FABAFDF6" authority="Wunderlich, 2012" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[937,1383,541,563]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonoburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC4DFDC3FBABFDF6" box="[937,1142,541,562]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Lagonoburmops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FB65FDC3FABAFDF6" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1153,1383,541,563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="157 - 232" refId="ref12807" refString="Wunderlich J. 2012. On the fossil spider (Araneae) fauna in Cretaceous ambers, with descriptions of new taxa from Myanmar (Burma) and Jordan, and on the relationships of the superfamily Leptonetoidea. Beitrage zur Araneologie 7: 157 - 232." type="journal article" year="2012">Wunderlich, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FCDFFDE2FB66FD96" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[827,1211,572,594]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Picturmegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFDE2FC03FD95" box="[827,990,572,593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Picturmegops</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FC02FDE2FB66FD96" author="Wunderlich J" box="[998,1211,572,594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) comprised only of female specimens, because of: carapace piriform in outline, much longer than wide (carapace distinctly narrowed posteriorly, slightly wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FCDFFD69FC3CFD08" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[827,993,695,716]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Picturmegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFD69FC3CFD08" box="[827,993,695,716]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Picturmegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); leg setae not long and dense (legs densely covered with long setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FB33FD0BFA4EFD2E" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2012" box="[1239,1427,725,746]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Lagonoburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FB33FD0BFA4EFD2E" box="[1239,1427,725,746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Lagonoburmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Conspecific spiders have some morphological differences at different developmental stages (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FAB2FCCCFCA9FC82" author="Foelix RF" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refId="ref10860" refString="Foelix RF. 2011. Biology of spiders, 3 rd edn. New York: Oxford University Press." type="book" year="2011">Foelix, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It is difficult to judge whether an adult male and a juvenile are the same species, especially in fossils. Therefore, we have erected a new genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FCDFFC53FC08FC66" box="[827,981,909,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCDFFC53FC08FC66" box="[827,981,909,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on CNU-ARA-MA2020001.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB036FCFFDFFF97FCB7FC72FB8BF9CC" blockId="3.[827,1444,388,1544]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Besides 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC5AFC72FBBCFC05" box="[958,1121,940,961]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC5AFC72FBBCFC05" box="[958,1121,940,961]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, seven species belonging to five genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FBF0FC14FB2FFC24" authorityName="ESKOV &amp; WUNDERLICH" authorityYear="1995" box="[1044,1266,970,992]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lagonomegopidae</taxonomicName>
are known to have one or more apophyses on the male palpal tibia. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC41FBD6FA41FBD9" authority="Wunderlich, 2017" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2017" box="[933,1436,1032,1054]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Albiburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulipes">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC41FBD6FB62FBD9" box="[933,1215,1032,1053]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Albiburmops annulipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FB2CFBD6FA41FBD9" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1224,1436,1032,1054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="72 - 279" refId="ref12903" refString="Wunderlich J. 2017. New and rare fossil spiders (Araneae) in mid Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Burma), including the description of new extinct families of the suborders Mesothelae and Opisthothelae, as well as notes on the taxonomy, the evolution and the biogeography of the Mesothelae. Beitrage zur Araneologie 10: 72 - 279." type="journal article" year="2017">Wunderlich, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the carapace length is equal to its width, whereas the carapace is distinctly much longer than wide in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FCBBFBBAFBD8FBBD" box="[863,1029,1124,1145]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCBBFBBAFBD8FBBD" box="[863,1029,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FBDBFBBAFBC3FB5C" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Archaelagonops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="propinquus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FBDBFBBAFA7EFBBD" box="[1087,1443,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Archaelagonops propinquus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FCDFFB5CFBC3FB5C" author="Wunderlich J" box="[827,1054,1154,1176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FB81FB5CFBFBFB73" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Archaelagonops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scorsum">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FB81FB5CFA7EFB5C" box="[1125,1443,1154,1176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Archaelagonops scorsum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FCDFFB7FFBFBFB73" author="Wunderlich J" box="[827,1062,1185,1207]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the palpal tibia bears two apophyses, whereas there is only one in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FAE7FB1EFA41FB11" box="[1283,1436,1216,1237]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FAE7FB1EFA41FB11" box="[1283,1436,1216,1237]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC80FB01FCA8FAD7" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Cymbiolagonops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cymbiocalcar">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC80FB01FB2BFB30" box="[868,1270,1246,1268]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Cymbiolagonops cymbiocalcar</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FAE7FB01FCA8FAD7" author="Wunderlich J" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the palpal tibia bears a divided apophysis, whereas the 
<collectionCode id="ED1EAE39FFDFFF97FC07FAC2FBC7FAF5" box="[995,1050,1308,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">RTA</collectionCode>
is undivided in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FB12FAC2FA46FAF5" box="[1270,1435,1308,1329]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FB12FAC2FA46FAF5" box="[1270,1435,1308,1329]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In? 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC8FFAE4FAB7FA8B" authority="Wunderlich, 2017" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2017" box="[875,1386,1338,1360]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Parviburmops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigibber">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC8FFAE4FB5BFA8B" box="[875,1158,1338,1359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Parviburmops bigibber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FB74FAE4FAB7FA8B" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1168,1386,1338,1360]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="72 - 279" refId="ref12903" refString="Wunderlich J. 2017. New and rare fossil spiders (Araneae) in mid Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Burma), including the description of new extinct families of the suborders Mesothelae and Opisthothelae, as well as notes on the taxonomy, the evolution and the biogeography of the Mesothelae. Beitrage zur Araneologie 10: 72 - 279." type="journal article" year="2017">Wunderlich, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the tibial apophysis is situated on the ventral surface, but is on the retrolateral surface in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FB19FAA6FA41FA49" box="[1277,1436,1400,1421]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FB19FAA6FA41FA49" box="[1277,1436,1400,1421]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC84FA48FAB7FA68" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[864,1386,1430,1452]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Paxillomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC84FA48FB5EFA6F" box="[864,1155,1430,1451]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Paxillomegops longipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FB69FA48FAB7FA68" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1165,1386,1430,1452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and? 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FCA2FA6BFAFFFA0F" authority="Wunderlich, 2015" authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2015" box="[838,1314,1461,1483]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Paxillomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FCA2FA6BFB8CFA0E" box="[838,1105,1461,1482]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Paxillomegops brevipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E4B0DFFDFFF97FBB2FA6BFAFFFA0F" author="Wunderlich J" box="[1110,1314,1461,1483]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" pagination="21 - 408" refId="ref12855" refString="Wunderlich J. 2015. On the evolution and the classification of spiders, the Mesozoic spider faunas, and descriptions of new Cretaceous taxa mainly in amber from Myanmar (Burma) (Arachnida: Araneae). Beitrage zur Araneologie 9: 21 - 408." type="journal article" year="2015">Wunderlich, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the palpal tibia bears numerous short peg bristles, which are lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F4D7FFFDFFF97FC52FA2DFB92F9CC" box="[950,1103,1523,1544]" class="Arachnida" family="Lagonomegopidae" genus="Scopomegops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97BEAEEFFDFFF97FC52FA2DFB92F9CC" box="[950,1103,1523,1544]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Scopomegops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
